I think we don't attempt to reconnect because the status is already "bonded" with eg this bootnode, even though peer count is zero

 DiscoveryPeer{status=bonded, enode=enode://cb
baacaf..., firstDiscovered=1701153716532, lastContacted=1701153716572, lastSeen=1701153716899},

so it's not a bondingCandidate per RecursivePeerRefreshState

```
    private boolean isBondingCandidate() {
      return !bondingComplete && !bondingStarted && peer.getStatus() == PeerDiscoveryStatus.KNOWN;
    }
```
